commit.message:
fix `--index-url` handling for Poetry 1.8 - second try (#270)

- if PyPI is disabled the highest prio source get `--index-url`, others get `--extra-index-url`
- if PyPI is enabled we just do not use `--index-url`, all other source get `--extra-index-url`
- put `--index-url` before `--extra-index-url` to work around a pip bug

fix `--index-url` handling for Poetry 1.8 - second try (#270)

- if PyPI is disabled the highest prio source get `--index-url`, others get `--extra-index-url`
- if PyPI is enabled we just do not use `--index-url`, all other source get `--extra-index-url`
- put `--index-url` before `--extra-index-url` to work around a pip bug

commit.message:
fix `--index-url` handling for Poetry 1.8:
- With Poetry 1.8 the source priority `default` is deprecated so that the first primary source has to take its place and be exported as `--index-url` instead of `--extra-index-url`.
- Bump required Poetry version so that we do not have to keep two implementations.
